{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-template-jsx","path":"/common-gotchas-when-mutating-a-slice","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<h1 id=\"common-gotchas-when-mutating-a-slice\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#common-gotchas-when-mutating-a-slice\" aria-label=\"common gotchas when mutating a slice permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Common gotchas when mutating a slice</h1>\n<p>Mutating slices in Go can be a bit confusing.</p>\n<p>It's generally known that slices are a reference an underlying array. But when it comes to mutating a slice, there are some very common gotchas that can trip you up. Let's look at three scenarios.</p>\n<h2 id=\"from-inside-a-function\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#from-inside-a-function\" aria-label=\"from inside a function permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>From inside a function</h2>\n<p>In Go, all variables are passed by value, meaning the function body will receive a copy.</p>\n<p>When you pass a slice to a function, the variable (slice descriptor), is a <strong>copy of the caller's reference</strong> to the underlying array (by <code class=\"language-text\">caller</code> I mean the place where the function is being called).</p>\n<p>So if you try to append to the slice inside the function, you are actually appending to a duplicate of the original reference. The caller's slice will remain unaffected.</p>\n<p>In the example below, we try to append a value to a slice, using the <code class=\"language-text\">addNum</code> function. Unfortunately, after calling <code class=\"language-text\">addNum</code>, the slice hasn't changed.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"go\"><pre class=\"language-go\"><code class=\"language-go\"><span class=\"token comment\">// THIS WON'T WORK</span>\nmySlice <span class=\"token operator\">:=</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span><span class=\"token builtin\">int</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span><span class=\"token number\">1</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span><span class=\"token number\">2</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span><span class=\"token number\">3</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"token keyword\">func</span> addNum <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>s <span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span><span class=\"token builtin\">int</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> num <span class=\"token builtin\">int</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n\ts <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token function\">append</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>s<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> num<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"token function\">addNum</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>mySlice<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token number\">4</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n\nfmt<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">Println</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>mySlice<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n\n<span class=\"token comment\">// --> [1 2 3]</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>To successfully append to the slice, the function must return its copy of the slice. You then assign it to the original slice.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"go\"><pre class=\"language-go\"><code class=\"language-go\">mySlice <span class=\"token operator\">:=</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span><span class=\"token builtin\">int</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span><span class=\"token number\">1</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span><span class=\"token number\">2</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span><span class=\"token number\">3</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"token keyword\">func</span> addNum <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>s <span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span><span class=\"token builtin\">int</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> num <span class=\"token builtin\">int</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span><span class=\"token builtin\">int</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n\t<span class=\"token keyword\">return</span> <span class=\"token function\">append</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>s<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> num<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n\nmySlice <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token function\">addNum</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>mySlice<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token number\">4</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n\nfmt<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">Println</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>mySlice<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n\n<span class=\"token comment\">// --> [1 2 3 4]</span></code></pre></div>\n<h2 id=\"from-inside-a-for-loop\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#from-inside-a-for-loop\" aria-label=\"from inside a for loop permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>From inside a for-loop</h2>\n<p>When ranging over a slice, the variable referencing each value points to <strong>a copy of the value</strong>. If you try to mutate the value at a given index with this variable, it will not work. Once you leave the scope of the for-loop, you'll find the slice was unaffected.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"go\"><pre class=\"language-go\"><code class=\"language-go\"><span class=\"token comment\">// THIS WON'T WORK</span>\nsomePeople <span class=\"token operator\">:=</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span><span class=\"token builtin\">string</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span><span class=\"token string\">\"Ada\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"Grace\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"Charles\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"token keyword\">for</span> <span class=\"token boolean\">_</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> name <span class=\"token operator\">:=</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">range</span> somePeople <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n\tname <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> strings<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">ToUpper</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>name<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n\nfmt<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">Println</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>somePeople<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n\n<span class=\"token comment\">// --> [\"Ada\" \"Grace\" \"Charles\"]</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>For the mutation to stick, you must use bracket notation instead:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"go\"><pre class=\"language-go\"><code class=\"language-go\">somePeople <span class=\"token operator\">:=</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span><span class=\"token builtin\">string</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span><span class=\"token string\">\"Ada\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"Grace\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"Charles\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"token keyword\">for</span> i<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> name <span class=\"token operator\">:=</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">range</span> somePeople <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n\tsomePeople<span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span>i<span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> strings<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">ToUpper</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>name<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n\nfmt<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">Println</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>somePeople<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n\n<span class=\"token comment\">// --> [\"ADA\" \"GRACE\" \"CHARLES\"]</span></code></pre></div>\n<h2 id=\"when-using-variables\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#when-using-variables\" aria-label=\"when using variables permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>When using variables</h2>\n<p>This is similar to the for-loop example. Any changes to a slice require the use of bracket notation. <strong>Variables will point to copies of the value</strong> at a given index, meaning any changes to that variable will not affect the slice.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"go\"><pre class=\"language-go\"><code class=\"language-go\"><span class=\"token comment\">// THIS WON'T WORK</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">type</span> food <span class=\"token keyword\">struct</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n\tname   <span class=\"token builtin\">string</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n\npantry <span class=\"token operator\">:=</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span>food<span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n\t<span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>name<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"banana\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n\t<span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>name<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"satsuma\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n\t<span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>name<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"kiwi\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n\ntoChange <span class=\"token operator\">:=</span> pantry<span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span><span class=\"token number\">2</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span> <span class=\"token comment\">// this makes a copy!</span>\ntoChange <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> food<span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>name<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"strawberry\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n\nfmt<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">Println</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>pantry<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n\n<span class=\"token comment\">// --> [{banana} {satsuma} {kiwi}]</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>With bracket notation, it works.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"go\"><pre class=\"language-go\"><code class=\"language-go\"><span class=\"token keyword\">type</span> food <span class=\"token keyword\">struct</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n\tname   <span class=\"token builtin\">string</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n\npantry <span class=\"token operator\">:=</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span>food<span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n\t<span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>name<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"banana\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n\t<span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>name<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"satsuma\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n\t<span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>name<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"kiwi\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n\npantry<span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span><span class=\"token number\">2</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> food<span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>name<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"strawberry\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n\nfmt<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">Println</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>pantry<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n\n<span class=\"token comment\">// --> [{banana} {satsuma} {strawberry}]</span></code></pre></div>","timeToRead":2,"excerpt":"Common gotchas when mutating a slice Mutating slices in Go can be a bit confusing. It's generally known that slices are a reference an…","frontmatter":{"title":"Common gotchas when mutating a slice","date":"2020-10-28 15:16:13 +0000","categories":["go"],"tags":["go","golang"],"description":null,"keywords":"go, golang","author":"Mina Gyimah","cover":{"childImageSharp":{"fixed":{"base64":"data:image/png;base64,iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAABQAAAAPCAYAAADkmO9VAAAACXBIWXMAAAsTAAALEwEAmpwYAAAAZ0lEQVQ4y2Mw5v//n5qYYdRAODbiw60JnxwDPg2GvAhsBKP58BuK04UgzRai//9biUNoM2EIbSJAhgtBWJ/r/3831f//Yx3//4+w/v8/yvb//2i7//+tJSCWDbyXqRopNDFwNOsRjQHOdKSa6R2eoAAAAABJRU5ErkJggg==","width":540,"height":400,"src":"/static/18b0edfdfa96fadbadd7955f1202cbd7/819a5/go.png","srcSet":"/static/18b0edfdfa96fadbadd7955f1202cbd7/819a5/go.png 1x"}}}},"fields":{"slug":"/common-gotchas-when-mutating-a-slice","date":"2020-10-28T15:16:13.000Z"}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/common-gotchas-when-mutating-a-slice","nexttitle":"Persistent Data Structures","nextslug":"/persistent-data-structures","prevtitle":"Useful Python libraries For Natural Processing","prevslug":"/useful-python-libraries-for-natural-processing","tagList":["abstraction","OOP","Class","java","collection","API","Map","HashMap","LinkedHashMap","TreeMap","Python","cli","args","argparse","javascript","es6","beginner","codenewbie","Primary_key","implementation","Composite_key","language-support","localization","internationalization","linux","file permissions","Project Euler","Algortithms","SQL","database","commands","GO","Datatypes","Variables","Constants","HTML5","Web development","tricks","NumpPy","array","python","NLP","libraries","text processing","go","golang","data-structure","optimization","java 7","Java 8","comparison","mkdir(make-dir) and rmdir(remove-dir command) command","nodejs","backend","frontend","postgres","mac","installation","games","gamedev","memory","html","bootstrap","web development","data","strings","final","finally","finalize","Git","GitLens","VS Code Extension","CSS","Images","Image Display","CSS Variables","JavaScript","sort","localeCompare","Responsive Fonts","CSS Fonts","interface","default method","static static","plot","spring boot","controller","annotation","mvc","rest","random","List","Set","Queue","hacktoberfest","python3","features","set","hashset","treeset","linkedhashset","list","array list","linked list","vector","slice","delete","one-liner","string","input-stream","nan","infinity","positive-infinity","negative-infinity","ci","travis-ci","travis","type-error","dict","pypi","pypi-stats","python-with","with statement","modules","python-modules","tags","doctype","meta","viewpor